---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy - Sun Synergy Contracts"
  description="How Sun Synergy Contracts collects, uses, and protects your personal data in accordance with Malaysia's Personal Data Protection Act 2010 (PDPA)."
>
  <main class="min-h-screen w-full space-y-5">

    <section class="relative isolate mx-auto w-full py-12 grid place-items-center mt-36">
      <div class="space-y-2">
        <p class="text-xs text-[#FAFAFA] mx-auto text-center uppercase">Legal</p>
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl xl:text-6xl text-[#FAFAFA] font-serif mx-auto text-center font-bold">Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="text-sm text-[#FAFAFA]/60 mx-auto text-center mt-2">Last updated: 6 May 2026</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <div class="px-6 py-20 lg:px-8">
        <article class="invert brightness-0 text-justify max-w-3xl mx-auto prose prose-sm prose-headings:font-medium lg:prose-headings:font-medium">

          <h2>1. About This Policy</h2>
          <p>This Privacy Policy explains how <strong>Sun Synergy Contracts Sdn Bhd</strong> (Company No. 1382832-A) collects, uses, discloses, and protects your personal data when you visit our website (<a href="https://sunsynergycontracts.com.my">sunsynergycontracts.com.my</a>), submit an enquiry, or interact with our marketing communications.</p>
          <p>We are committed to protecting your personal data in accordance with Malaysia's <strong>Personal Data Protection Act 2010 (PDPA)</strong>. By using our website or submitting your details to us, you consent to the collection and use of your information as described in this policy.</p>

          <h2>2. Data We Collect</h2>

          <h3>Information you provide to us</h3>
          <p>When you submit a quotation request, contact form, or WhatsApp enquiry, we may collect:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Full name</li>
            <li>Phone number (including WhatsApp)</li>
            <li>Email address</li>
            <li>Property address or general location (city/area)</li>
            <li>Type of property (e.g., terrace house, condominium, office)</li>
            <li>Services you are interested in (e.g., home renovation, interior design, kitchen cabinetry)</li>
            <li>Project timeline, budget range, or other details you choose to share</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>Information collected automatically</h3>
          <p>When you visit our website, we automatically collect certain technical and behavioural data through cookies and tracking tools, including:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>IP address and general geographic location</li>
            <li>Browser type and device type</li>
            <li>Pages visited, time spent on each page, and referring URL</li>
            <li>Clicks on calls-to-action (WhatsApp button, phone number, contact form)</li>
          </ul>
          <p>See Section 6 for details on the specific tools we use.</p>

          <h2>3. How We Use Your Data</h2>
          <p>We use the personal data you provide for the following purposes:</p>

          <h3>To respond to your enquiry</h3>
          <p>When you submit a quotation request or contact form, we use your details to follow up via phone, WhatsApp, or email to discuss your renovation project, arrange a site visit, and provide a written quotation.</p>

          <h3>To manage and nurture your enquiry</h3>
          <p>Your contact details and project information are stored in our customer relationship management (CRM) system. We may send follow-up messages via WhatsApp or email to update you on the status of your enquiry, share relevant project portfolios, or provide information about our services. You may opt out of follow-up communications at any time by replying STOP or by contacting us directly.</p>

          <h3>To fulfil your renovation contract</h3>
          <p>Once a project is underway, we use your details to coordinate site visits, communicate project progress, issue invoices, and manage the contractual relationship.</p>

          <h3>To improve our services and marketing</h3>
          <p>We analyse aggregated, anonymised data about how visitors use our website to improve site performance, identify high-interest pages, and refine our service offerings.</p>

          <h3>To run paid advertising campaigns</h3>
          <p>We use conversion tracking and audience tools provided by Google Ads and Meta (Facebook and Instagram) to measure the effectiveness of our paid advertisements and to show relevant ads to people who have previously expressed interest in our services. See Section 6 for full details.</p>

          <h2>4. Legal Basis for Processing</h2>
          <p>Under the PDPA 2010, we process your personal data on the following grounds:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Consent:</strong> When you voluntarily submit your details through our contact form, WhatsApp, or other enquiry channels, you are consenting to us processing that data to respond to your request.</li>
            <li><strong>Contractual necessity:</strong> When you engage us for a renovation project, processing your personal data is necessary to fulfil the contract.</li>
            <li><strong>Legitimate interest:</strong> We have a legitimate interest in following up on genuine renovation enquiries, improving our marketing effectiveness, and measuring advertising performance - provided this does not override your rights.</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>5. How Long We Keep Your Data</h2>
          <p>We retain your personal data for as long as is necessary for the purposes set out in this policy:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Enquiry data (no project awarded):</strong> Up to 12 months from the date of your last communication with us.</li>
            <li><strong>Project data (contract executed):</strong> Up to 7 years after project completion, in accordance with Malaysian accounting and legal requirements.</li>
            <li><strong>Marketing analytics data:</strong> As governed by the respective third-party platforms (Google, Meta); typically up to 26 months for analytics data.</li>
          </ul>
          <p>After the applicable retention period, your data will be securely deleted or anonymised.</p>

          <h2>6. Third-Party Tools & Data Sharing</h2>
          <p>We use the following third-party tools that may process your personal data. Each is subject to its own privacy policy.</p>

          <h3>Google Tag Manager & Google Analytics 4</h3>
          <p>We use Google Tag Manager to deploy and manage tracking scripts on our website, including Google Analytics 4 (GA4). GA4 tracks user behaviour on our site (pages visited, events triggered) using anonymised data. No personally identifiable information is sent to Google Analytics. <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Privacy Policy</a>.</p>

          <h3>Google Ads</h3>
          <p>We run paid search campaigns on Google. Google Ads conversion tracking records actions you take on our site after clicking an ad (e.g., submitting a contact form, clicking our phone number). We may also use Google's Customer Match and remarketing features to show ads to people who have previously visited our website. <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Privacy Policy</a>.</p>

          <h3>Meta Pixel (Facebook & Instagram)</h3>
          <p>We may use Meta Pixel to track conversions from Facebook and Instagram ads, to build lookalike audiences, and to retarget website visitors on Meta platforms. The pixel collects information about your actions on our website (e.g., page views, form submissions) and shares it with Meta in accordance with Meta's data policy. <a href="https://www.facebook.com/policy.php" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Meta Privacy Policy</a>.</p>

          <h3>CRM & Workflow Automation</h3>
          <p>Enquiry data you submit may be stored and processed in our CRM platform to manage follow-up communications, track lead status, and automate workflow notifications to our team. Data stored in the CRM is accessible only to authorised Sun Synergy Contracts personnel and is not sold or shared with third parties for their own marketing purposes.</p>

          <h3>WhatsApp Business</h3>
          <p>If you contact us or consent to follow-up via WhatsApp, your messages and phone number are processed through WhatsApp's platform, which is subject to Meta's privacy policy. We use WhatsApp to communicate project details, share quotations, and send follow-up updates related to your enquiry.</p>

          <h3>Email (Google Workspace)</h3>
          <p>We use Google Workspace (Gmail) for email communications. Emails you send us are stored on Google's servers and subject to <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google's Privacy Policy</a>.</p>

          <h2>7. Data Security</h2>
          <p>We take reasonable technical and organisational measures to protect your personal data against unauthorised access, disclosure, alteration, or destruction. Our website is served over HTTPS and access to CRM systems is restricted to authorised personnel only.</p>
          <p>No method of transmission over the internet is completely secure. While we strive to protect your data, we cannot guarantee its absolute security.</p>

          <h2>8. Your Rights Under the PDPA</h2>
          <p>Under Malaysia's Personal Data Protection Act 2010, you have the right to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Access</strong> the personal data we hold about you.</li>
            <li><strong>Correct</strong> any inaccurate or incomplete personal data.</li>
            <li><strong>Withdraw consent</strong> to the processing of your personal data at any time (this will not affect processing carried out before withdrawal).</li>
            <li><strong>Request deletion</strong> of your personal data, subject to our legal retention obligations.</li>
            <li><strong>Opt out</strong> of direct marketing communications.</li>
          </ul>
          <p>To exercise any of these rights, please contact our Data Protection Officer using the details in Section 10. We will respond to your request within 21 business days.</p>

          <h2>9. Children's Privacy</h2>
          <p>This website is not directed at children under the age of 18. We do not knowingly collect personal data from minors. If you believe a child has submitted personal data to us, please contact us and we will delete it promptly.</p>

          <h2>10. Contact & Data Requests</h2>
          <p>For any questions about this Privacy Policy, to exercise your data rights, or to opt out of marketing communications, please contact us at:</p>
          <p>
            <strong>Sun Synergy Contracts Sdn Bhd</strong><br />
            17C, Jalan PJS 1/33<br />
            Taman Petaling Utama<br />
            46150 Petaling Jaya, Selangor, Malaysia<br />
            <a href="mailto:info@sunsynergycontracts.com.my">info@sunsynergycontracts.com.my</a><br />
            <a href="tel:+60128773999">+60 12-877 3999</a>
          </p>

          <h2>11. Changes to This Policy</h2>
          <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices or legal requirements. The "Last updated" date at the top of this page will reflect the most recent revision. Continued use of our website after any changes constitutes your acceptance of the updated policy.</p>

        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>
</BaseLayout>
